
Step 1 — Create project folder:
mkdir ~/docker-nginx
cd ~/docker-nginx

Step 2 — Create your HTML file:
nano index.html
type code inside index.html

Step 3 — Create Dockerfile:
nano Dockerfile
Type this:

FROM nginx
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
EXPOSE 80

Save Ctrl+S then Ctrl+X

Step 4 — Build image:
docker build -t mywebsite .

Now run your website container:
docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name mywebsite-container mywebsite

Part   					Meaning
-d	               	  	run in background
-p 8080:80			your port 8080 → container port 80
--name mywebsite-container 	container name
mywebsite			your image

Then open your browser and go to:
http://localhost:8080

