Simple — just edit your HTML file and push!

Step 1 — Edit your HTML:
bashcd ~/docker-nginx
vim index.html
Make your changes!

Step 2 — Rebuild Docker image:
bashdocker build -t mywebsite .

Step 3 — Stop old container:
bashdocker stop mywebsite-container
docker rm mywebsite-container

Step 4 — Run new container:
bashdocker run -d -p 8080:80 --name mywebsite-container mywebsite
Step 5 — Check browser:

http://localhost:8080
Your changes are live! 🌐

Step 6 — Push to GitHub:
bashgit pull
git add .
git commit -m "Updated website design"
git push

Simple flow:
Edit HTML → rebuild image → restart container → check browser → push to GitHub

